00:36:59.390 --> 00:37:02.610 align:middle line:84%
there's an enzyme
called collagenase that

00:37:02.610 --> 00:37:04.250 align:middle line:90%
increases as we get older.

00:37:04.250 --> 00:37:07.960 align:middle line:84%
And collagenase means
it breaks down collagen.

00:37:07.960 --> 00:37:10.860 align:middle line:84%
Elastinase means
it breaks elastin.

00:37:10.860 --> 00:37:13.100 align:middle line:84%
And the reason why it
increases as it gets older

00:37:13.100 --> 00:37:16.240 align:middle line:84%
is because the microbes on
your face, as we get older,

00:37:16.240 --> 00:37:19.170 align:middle line:84%
start to decrease because of
all the products that we have.

00:37:19.170 --> 00:37:21.660 align:middle line:84%
So you put the same microbes
that you had on your face

00:37:21.660 --> 00:37:24.000 align:middle line:84%
when you were 18,
and guess what?

00:37:24.000 --> 00:37:25.522 align:middle line:84%
All that stuff
starts to go away.

00:37:25.522 --> 00:37:26.730 align:middle line:90%
And that's what we're seeing.

00:37:26.730 --> 00:37:29.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Wow, that
is fascinating.

00:37:29.910 --> 00:37:33.770 align:middle line:84%
And you also have protocols
for teeth and gums,

00:37:33.770 --> 00:37:35.990 align:middle line:84%
but before we get to
that because that's

00:37:35.990 --> 00:37:37.500 align:middle line:84%
another story, a
fascinating story.

00:37:37.500 --> 00:37:39.450 align:middle line:84%
And I've been using this
toothpaste for about a year.

00:37:39.450 --> 00:37:40.225 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: Yeah, the Oralive.

00:37:40.225 --> 00:37:40.770 align:middle line:90%
It's great.

00:37:40.770 --> 00:37:41.395 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:37:41.395 --> 00:37:42.231 align:middle line:90%
It looks like mud.

00:37:42.231 --> 00:37:43.730 align:middle line:84%
You're brushing
