00:37:43.730 --> 00:37:45.970 align:middle line:84%
We'll talk about that
story, but let's talk

00:37:45.970 --> 00:37:48.400 align:middle line:84%
about the notion
of how they have

00:37:48.400 --> 00:37:50.740 align:middle line:84%
eat right type for
your blood type,

00:37:50.740 --> 00:37:52.840 align:middle line:84%
eat right for your
metabolic type;

00:37:52.840 --> 00:37:56.800 align:middle line:84%
you're saying that
what's really important

00:37:56.800 --> 00:37:59.387 align:middle line:84%
is to eat right for
your microbe type.

00:37:59.387 --> 00:38:00.220 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: That's right.

00:38:00.220 --> 00:38:02.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And let's talk about
that for a minute because here

00:38:02.970 --> 00:38:08.149 align:middle line:84%
you have the one size fits all
if you eat a vegan, raw diet,

00:38:08.149 --> 00:38:09.440 align:middle line:90%
you're going to live to be 100.

00:38:09.440 --> 00:38:11.840 align:middle line:84%
Well, some people
would die on that diet.

00:38:11.840 --> 00:38:16.220 align:middle line:84%
Same thing, the Paleo Diet,
others aren't compatible.

00:38:16.220 --> 00:38:18.444 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about it from
a microbial point of view.

00:38:18.444 --> 00:38:20.110 align:middle line:84%
>>ROM: From the
microbial point of view,

00:38:20.110 --> 00:38:22.090 align:middle line:84%
in order to eat
a raw vegan diet,

00:38:22.090 --> 00:38:24.350 align:middle line:84%
you actually have to
have the right microbes.

00:38:24.350 --> 00:38:27.500 align:middle line:84%
And these microbes are
from a microbe type,

00:38:27.500 --> 00:38:29.990 align:middle line:84%
let's call them rumen
type because they

00:38:29.990 --> 00:38:33.310 align:middle line:84%
are good at breaking
down cellulose.

00:38:33.310 --> 00:38:36.380 align:middle line:84%
Approximately 20% percent
of the-- this whole science

00:38:36.380 --> 00:38:37.190 align:middle line:90%
is brand new.

00:38:37.190 --> 00:38:37.940 align:middle line:90%
I mean, literally.

00:38:37.940 --> 00:38:42.210 align:middle line:84%
This study came out
in July of 2012,

00:38:42.210 --> 00:38:43.715 align:middle line:90%
and also another study in 2011.

00:38:43.715 --> 00:38:45.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Brand new, OK.

00:38:45.020 --> 00:38:48.410 align:middle line:84%
>>ROM: They're starting to
find out that at the moment,

00:38:48.410 --> 00:38:51.660 align:middle line:84%
at this time, we can break
down that the human body has

00:38:51.660 --> 00:38:53.460 align:middle line:84%
three types of
microbes in our gut.

00:38:53.460 --> 00:38:57.490 align:middle line:84%
We have the F type, the
Firmiculites, F for fat.

00:38:57.490 --> 00:38:59.620 align:middle line:84%
If you have a predominance
of this F type,

00:38:59.620 --> 00:39:01.620 align:middle line:84%
you get fat, because
these microbes

00:39:01.620 --> 00:39:04.120 align:middle line:84%
are really good at breaking
down the simple sugars

00:39:04.120 --> 00:39:06.800 align:middle line:84%
and assimilating the simple
sugars inside your body.

00:39:06.800 --> 00:39:08.480 align:middle line:84%
Then you have the
B type for bony.

00:39:08.480 --> 00:39:11.260 align:middle line:84%
Those are called the
Bacteroidetes, or something

00:39:11.260 --> 00:39:12.180 align:middle line:90%
like that.

00:39:12.180 --> 00:39:13.350 align:middle line:90%
I can't say it right now.

00:39:13.350 --> 00:39:15.480 align:middle line:84%
But it's the B type for
bony, and those people

00:39:15.480 --> 00:39:16.690 align:middle line:90%
tend to be lean.

00:39:16.690 --> 00:39:18.640 align:middle line:84%
And then you have the
R type for the rumens.

00:39:18.640 --> 00:39:19.650 align:middle line:90%
Those are like the cows.

00:39:19.650 --> 00:39:22.540 align:middle line:84%
They eat the raw foods
and the cellulose.

00:39:22.540 --> 00:39:25.210 align:middle line:84%
But the people that are lean
have a high predominance

00:39:25.210 --> 00:39:29.360 align:middle line:84%
of the B type
microbes in your body.

00:39:29.360 --> 00:39:32.070 align:middle line:84%
And you can actually
shift the obesity

00:39:32.070 --> 00:39:36.770 align:middle line:84%
to lean barrier by increasing
the amount of B type microbes

00:39:36.770 --> 00:39:39.320 align:middle line:84%
in your body, because they're
very good at breaking down

00:39:39.320 --> 00:39:42.460 align:middle line:84%
proteins and complex
carbohydrates.

00:39:42.460 --> 00:39:45.810 align:middle line:84%
And what they do is they
break them down for energy,

00:39:45.810 --> 00:39:47.880 align:middle line:84%
and they don't
get stored as fat.

00:39:47.880 --> 00:39:48.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:39:48.820 --> 00:39:51.710 align:middle line:84%
>>ROM: The way they found
this out was in 2008,

00:39:51.710 --> 00:39:54.950 align:middle line:84%
a scientist by the name of
Jeremy Nicholson from Oxford,

00:39:54.950 --> 00:39:57.670 align:middle line:84%
England, produced a
study in "Nature,"

00:39:57.670 --> 00:40:00.250 align:middle line:84%
which is the most prestigious
journal in the world,

00:40:00.250 --> 00:40:04.200 align:middle line:84%
trying to find out the
most-- healthiest people

00:40:04.200 --> 00:40:05.450 align:middle line:90%
in the planet.

00:40:05.450 --> 00:40:07.430 align:middle line:84%
And he looked at five
different regions.

00:40:07.430 --> 00:40:12.130 align:middle line:84%
He looked at the United States,
the United Kingdom, Japan,

00:40:12.130 --> 00:40:15.440 align:middle line:84%
China, and areas
of Eastern Europe.

00:40:15.440 --> 00:40:17.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The
Balkans and so forth.

00:40:17.290 --> 00:40:17.810 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: Yeah.

00:40:17.810 --> 00:40:22.350 align:middle line:84%
And he found out there were,
ah, an area of the world where

00:40:22.350 --> 00:40:24.300 align:middle line:84%
people lived the
shortest, and there

00:40:24.300 --> 00:40:26.830 align:middle line:84%
was an area of the world
that lived the longest.

00:40:26.830 --> 00:40:29.249 align:middle line:84%
And guess where the
people lived the shortest?

00:40:29.249 --> 00:40:29.790 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: US?

00:40:29.790 --> 00:40:32.600 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: Houston, Texas.

00:40:32.600 --> 00:40:39.000 align:middle line:84%
They had a diet basically of
dead animal flesh and a lot

00:40:39.000 --> 00:40:41.610 align:middle line:84%
of fat and a lot
of processed foods,

00:40:41.610 --> 00:40:44.160 align:middle line:84%
and a lot of foods that were
actually genetically modified,

00:40:44.160 --> 00:40:47.080 align:middle line:84%
and foods that were
laden with hormones.

00:40:47.080 --> 00:40:52.060 align:middle line:84%
Versus this area in
southern China called Yunan,

00:40:52.060 --> 00:40:54.040 align:middle line:84%
people were so poor they
couldn't afford meat,

00:40:54.040 --> 00:40:55.660 align:middle line:84%
so they were kind
of like vegetarians

00:40:55.660 --> 00:41:00.340 align:middle line:90%
not by choice, but by economics.

00:41:00.340 --> 00:41:02.370 align:middle line:84%
And they fermented a
lot of their foods,

00:41:02.370 --> 00:41:04.340 align:middle line:84%
and they didn't
refrigerate a lot of foods.

00:41:04.340 --> 00:41:06.300 align:middle line:84%
So they eated a lot of
microbes in their foods,

00:41:06.300 --> 00:41:09.560 align:middle line:84%
but they ate a lot
of complex starches

00:41:09.560 --> 00:41:11.660 align:middle line:84%
and complex carbohydrates
in their diet.

00:41:11.660 --> 00:41:13.350 align:middle line:84%
And they found out
that these people

00:41:13.350 --> 00:41:16.770 align:middle line:84%
lived to an average
age of like 78 years.

00:41:16.770 --> 00:41:19.460 align:middle line:84%
And they had very low
incidence of diabetes,

00:41:19.460 --> 00:41:21.360 align:middle line:84%
had very low incidence
of heart disease,

00:41:21.360 --> 00:41:23.800 align:middle line:84%
had very low
incidence of cancer.

00:41:23.800 --> 00:41:29.020 align:middle line:84%
Versus the ones in the United
States based on their microbes,

00:41:29.020 --> 00:41:31.150 align:middle line:84%
they had a high
incidence of diabetes,

00:41:31.150 --> 00:41:33.930 align:middle line:84%
they had a high
incidence of obesity,

00:41:33.930 --> 00:41:36.650 align:middle line:84%
had a high incidence of heart
disease, and high incidence

00:41:36.650 --> 00:41:37.540 align:middle line:90%
of cancer.

00:41:37.540 --> 00:41:40.460 align:middle line:84%
And they were apt to live
only till about 72 years.

00:41:40.460 --> 00:41:42.630 align:middle line:84%
It got to the point
where these scientists,

00:41:42.630 --> 00:41:44.840 align:middle line:84%
they found out what
microbe type you are just

00:41:44.840 --> 00:41:47.470 align:middle line:84%
by measuring the
metabolites in your urine.

00:41:47.470 --> 00:41:50.090 align:middle line:84%
And they called it
originally the metabolome.

00:41:50.090 --> 00:41:51.785 align:middle line:90%
It's now called a microbiome.

00:41:51.785 --> 00:41:53.410 align:middle line:84%
The metabolome,
because the metabolites

00:41:53.410 --> 00:41:55.800 align:middle line:84%
determined the kind of microbes
that you had in your gut

00:41:55.800 --> 00:41:57.660 align:middle line:84%
that were producing
the metabolites.

00:41:57.660 --> 00:42:00.590 align:middle line:84%
And so by looking at the
microbe type, they can tell,

00:42:00.590 --> 00:42:03.690 align:middle line:84%
they go, we don't even
know where these people are

00:42:03.690 --> 00:42:07.090 align:middle line:84%
because of the microbes
they had in their urine

00:42:07.090 --> 00:42:09.290 align:middle line:84%
and in their body,
we know that they're

00:42:09.290 --> 00:42:11.340 align:middle line:90%
going to live till about 72.

00:42:11.340 --> 00:42:14.510 align:middle line:84%
They're going to die of
either heart disease, cancer,

00:42:14.510 --> 00:42:17.780 align:middle line:84%
or diabetes, or versus they're
going to die of old age,

00:42:17.780 --> 00:42:21.600 align:middle line:84%
they're going to die of
a fall or something like.

00:42:21.600 --> 00:42:25.590 align:middle line:84%
So it's down to a science
now that basically

00:42:25.590 --> 00:42:27.380 align:middle line:84%
based on the kind
of microbes that you

00:42:27.380 --> 00:42:29.400 align:middle line:84%
have in your gut,
scientists can actually

00:42:29.400 --> 00:42:31.442 align:middle line:84%
tell when you're
going to die and what

00:42:31.442 --> 00:42:32.400 align:middle line:90%
you're going to die of.

00:42:32.400 --> 00:42:34.774 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Now that's interesting
because you were talking

00:42:34.774 --> 00:42:38.120 align:middle line:84%
about metabolic
type a moment ago.

00:42:38.120 --> 00:42:42.170 align:middle line:84%
It sounds like the metabolic
type might more closely

00:42:42.170 --> 00:42:46.110 align:middle line:84%
align with the microbial type
diet than, say, the blood type.

00:42:46.110 --> 00:42:48.400 align:middle line:84%
Or is it all kind
of interconnected?

00:42:48.400 --> 00:42:49.940 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: It's all interconnected.

00:42:49.940 --> 00:42:53.070 align:middle line:84%
The main difference between the
metabolic type and the blood

00:42:53.070 --> 00:42:55.560 align:middle line:84%
type is you cannot
choose your blood type.

00:42:55.560 --> 00:42:58.640 align:middle line:84%
If you're blood type
A versus blood type O,

00:42:58.640 --> 00:43:00.390 align:middle line:90%
you're born with that.

00:43:00.390 --> 00:43:02.550 align:middle line:84%
The metabolic type, if
you're a high metabolic rate

00:43:02.550 --> 00:43:06.380 align:middle line:84%
versus a low metabolic rate
versus a meso metabolic rate,

00:43:06.380 --> 00:43:07.832 align:middle line:90%
you can't change that.

00:43:07.832 --> 00:43:09.540 align:middle line:84%
The beautiful thing
with the microbe type

00:43:09.540 --> 00:43:11.160 align:middle line:90%
is you can completely change it.

00:43:11.160 --> 00:43:12.190 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You can.

00:43:12.190 --> 00:43:14.615 align:middle line:84%
And you were also talking
about how in Houston they

00:43:14.615 --> 00:43:17.160 align:middle line:84%
ate a lot of, I think you
said dead animal flesh,

00:43:17.160 --> 00:43:21.040 align:middle line:84%
but in reality, most of the
population on the planet

00:43:21.040 --> 00:43:22.780 align:middle line:90%
eat some kind of animal protein.

00:43:22.780 --> 00:43:23.613 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: That's right.

00:43:23.613 --> 00:43:29.055 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that is necessary
for one or two of the--

00:43:29.055 --> 00:43:29.930 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: Microbe types.

00:43:29.930 --> 00:43:30.370 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: -microbe types.

00:43:30.370 --> 00:43:31.210 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: That's right.

00:43:31.210 --> 00:43:33.270 align:middle line:84%
Animal flesh and
animal protein is

00:43:33.270 --> 00:43:36.390 align:middle line:84%
very necessary for one or
two of the microbe types.

00:43:36.390 --> 00:43:40.487 align:middle line:84%
And when I say dead animal
flesh, I personally eat meat,

00:43:40.487 --> 00:43:42.070 align:middle line:84%
but I don't like to
eat a lot of meat.

00:43:42.070 --> 00:43:43.970 align:middle line:84%
And I certainly
don't eat meat that's

00:43:43.970 --> 00:43:47.620 align:middle line:84%
been unconsciously raised,
because the steroids

00:43:47.620 --> 00:43:50.030 align:middle line:84%
in the meat and the
consciousness in which

00:43:50.030 --> 00:43:52.825 align:middle line:84%
that meat was raised, it's
actually in the bloodstream

00:43:52.825 --> 00:43:55.400 align:middle line:84%
and is carried on
through little molecules.

00:43:55.400 --> 00:43:59.370 align:middle line:84%
So I like to eat meat that was
grass fed and humanely raised.

00:43:59.370 --> 00:44:03.780 align:middle line:84%
Given that, we can
change the microbe type.

00:44:03.780 --> 00:44:06.200 align:middle line:84%
We know that we can change
the microbe type because they

00:44:06.200 --> 00:44:08.260 align:middle line:84%
can actually transfer
microbes from one

00:44:08.260 --> 00:44:11.390 align:middle line:84%
human to another human and
completely shift the way

00:44:11.390 --> 00:44:13.050 align:middle line:90%
they eat and what they crave.

00:44:13.050 --> 00:44:14.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So your
body-- now how do

00:44:14.800 --> 00:44:17.600 align:middle line:84%
you introduce the
different kind of microbe

00:44:17.600 --> 00:44:20.250 align:middle line:90%
into the body, number one.

00:44:20.250 --> 00:44:22.580 align:middle line:84%
First you have to determine
what your microbe type is.

00:44:22.580 --> 00:44:24.040 align:middle line:84%
You have to determine
the dominance

00:44:24.040 --> 00:44:25.280 align:middle line:90%
of what's in your body, right?

00:44:25.280 --> 00:44:26.040 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: They actually don't.

00:44:26.040 --> 00:44:26.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You don't?

00:44:26.320 --> 00:44:28.380 align:middle line:84%
>>ROM: I mean, that's
just thinking too much.

00:44:28.380 --> 00:44:28.980 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so how
do you introduce--

00:44:28.980 --> 00:44:31.000 align:middle line:84%
>>ROM: You'll know the microbe
type in your body just the way

00:44:31.000 --> 00:44:31.666 align:middle line:90%
your body looks.

00:44:31.666 --> 00:44:32.400 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I see.

00:44:32.400 --> 00:44:32.900 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:44:32.900 --> 00:44:38.130 align:middle line:84%
>>ROM: If you have low
energy and if you're obese

00:44:38.130 --> 00:44:40.250 align:middle line:84%
and you're eating
a lot of starches,

00:44:40.250 --> 00:44:45.010 align:middle line:84%
you're going to have the microbe
type that makes you obese

00:44:45.010 --> 00:44:46.992 align:middle line:84%
and makes you eat
a lot of starch.

00:44:46.992 --> 00:44:48.450 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter
what it's called.

00:44:48.450 --> 00:44:51.890 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So you can introduce
the countervailing microbe

00:44:51.890 --> 00:44:52.610 align:middle line:90%
set into it?

00:44:52.610 --> 00:44:53.470 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: That's right.

00:44:53.470 --> 00:44:55.440 align:middle line:84%
You can introduce a
countervailing microbe

00:44:55.440 --> 00:44:59.880 align:middle line:84%
set by getting the microbes
from the people that you like.

00:44:59.880 --> 00:45:02.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But how do you do get
microbes from people which--

00:45:02.420 --> 00:45:05.282 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: This is kind of gross.

00:45:05.282 --> 00:45:06.860 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It would have to be.

00:45:06.860 --> 00:45:09.160 align:middle line:84%
>>ROM: There's an amazing
doctor out at the University

00:45:09.160 --> 00:45:13.880 align:middle line:84%
of Minnesota, his name is
Doctor Khoruts, or Khoruts,

00:45:13.880 --> 00:45:15.690 align:middle line:90%
I can't pronounce his name.

00:45:15.690 --> 00:45:16.700 align:middle line:90%
He's a wonderful doctor.

00:45:16.700 --> 00:45:20.510 align:middle line:10%
He was able to cure
clostridium difficile, which

00:45:20.510 --> 00:45:24.640 align:middle line:10%
is a microbe inside the
gut that a lot of people

00:45:24.640 --> 00:45:27.850 align:middle line:10%
were getting like Crohn's
disease and ulcerative colitis.

00:45:27.850 --> 00:45:31.930 align:middle line:10%
And he was able to cure these
people-- in fact, a husband

00:45:31.930 --> 00:45:34.820 align:middle line:10%
and wife-- by introducing the
gut microbes from the husband

00:45:34.820 --> 00:45:38.890 align:middle line:10%
that didn't have this
disease into the wife

00:45:38.890 --> 00:45:41.410 align:middle line:10%
by taking his stool
sample, mixing it up

00:45:41.410 --> 00:45:45.910 align:middle line:10%
with a little saline, and then
feeding his wife the husband's

00:45:45.910 --> 00:45:48.335 align:middle line:10%
microbes through a feeding tube.

00:45:48.335 --> 00:45:49.710 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Through
a feeding tube?

00:45:49.710 --> 00:45:50.920 align:middle line:90%
Not the other way?

00:45:50.920 --> 00:45:51.420 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: No.

00:45:51.420 --> 00:45:52.271 align:middle line:90%
Not the other way.

00:45:52.271 --> 00:45:53.770 align:middle line:84%
Because you have
to get the microbes

00:45:53.770 --> 00:45:55.340 align:middle line:90%
inside the small intestine.

00:45:55.340 --> 00:45:57.840 align:middle line:84%
It's literally a procedure
called a fecal matter

00:45:57.840 --> 00:45:59.415 align:middle line:90%
transplant, a stool transplant.

00:45:59.415 --> 00:46:01.289 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, at least
it's a feeding tube.

00:46:01.289 --> 00:46:03.370 align:middle line:84%
>>ROM: Well, there's
a CPT code for it,

00:46:03.370 --> 00:46:05.720 align:middle line:84%
so Medicaid and
Medicare actually

00:46:05.720 --> 00:46:06.990 align:middle line:90%
reimburses people for it.

00:46:06.990 --> 00:46:07.740 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: They do?

00:46:07.740 --> 00:46:09.210 align:middle line:90%
But this has to be very rare.

00:46:09.210 --> 00:46:10.250 align:middle line:90%
How many--

00:46:10.250 --> 00:46:12.100 align:middle line:84%
>>ROM: Well, he's
trying to-- I'm

00:46:12.100 --> 00:46:15.080 align:middle line:84%
saying now, Dr. Khoruts,
you have a big fan here

00:46:15.080 --> 00:46:17.620 align:middle line:84%
and I'm trying to get
this out in the open.

00:46:17.620 --> 00:46:18.980 align:middle line:90%
Fecal matter transplant.

00:46:18.980 --> 00:46:19.590 align:middle line:90%
Google it.

00:46:19.590 --> 00:46:20.290 align:middle line:90%
It's amazing.

00:46:20.290 --> 00:46:21.873 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No, I mean
if you're talking

00:46:21.873 --> 00:46:23.920 align:middle line:84%
about being able
to literally change

00:46:23.920 --> 00:46:25.990 align:middle line:84%
the cravings and the
environment in your system

00:46:25.990 --> 00:46:29.400 align:middle line:84%
to change the way you
eat and you store fat,

00:46:29.400 --> 00:46:31.280 align:middle line:84%
that's going to be
incredibly valuable.

00:46:31.280 --> 00:46:32.900 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: I'm telling you, it is.

00:46:32.900 --> 00:46:34.150 align:middle line:90%
And here's the thing.

00:46:34.150 --> 00:46:36.370 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to resort
to a feeding tube.

00:46:36.370 --> 00:46:39.310 align:middle line:84%
You can actually-- OK, I
have to toot my own horn.

00:46:39.310 --> 00:46:41.230 align:middle line:84%
We're actually
making microbes that

00:46:41.230 --> 00:46:45.660 align:middle line:90%
feed off of these healthy foods.

00:46:45.660 --> 00:46:48.910 align:middle line:84%
With our ProAlive Probiotic
and our Active Detox Probiotic,

00:46:48.910 --> 00:46:51.230 align:middle line:84%
we actually-- because
these microbes

00:46:51.230 --> 00:46:56.290 align:middle line:84%
were grown on all organic,
vegan, plant-based foods,

00:46:56.290 --> 00:46:58.850 align:middle line:84%
these people starting to take
these probiotics, some of them

00:46:58.850 --> 00:47:00.270 align:middle line:90%
were saying, you know what?

00:47:00.270 --> 00:47:01.967 align:middle line:84%
My cravings for
sugar has gone down.

00:47:01.967 --> 00:47:04.550 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So their body type has
actually changed as a result?

00:47:04.550 --> 00:47:04.890 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: It's shifting.

00:47:04.890 --> 00:47:05.360 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:47:05.360 --> 00:47:06.230 align:middle line:90%
It's shifting as a result.

00:47:06.230 --> 00:47:07.938 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that
saves you the process.

00:47:07.938 --> 00:47:09.910 align:middle line:84%
>>ROM: That saves you
the process, right?

00:47:09.910 --> 00:47:10.100 align:middle line:90%
But--

00:47:10.100 --> 00:47:11.490 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And the
expense, I guess.

00:47:11.490 --> 00:47:13.240 align:middle line:84%
>>ROM: -you don't have
to buy our product.

00:47:13.240 --> 00:47:17.639 align:middle line:10%
All you need to do is find a
good, healthy fermented food

00:47:17.639 --> 00:47:19.180 align:middle line:10%
and start eating
that fermented food.

00:47:19.180 --> 00:47:22.950 align:middle line:84%
Because basically it's
going to be on a plant.

00:47:22.950 --> 00:47:24.730 align:middle line:90%
And fermented kefirs.

00:47:24.730 --> 00:47:28.220 align:middle line:84%
It'll be on goat's
milk or cow's milk.

00:47:28.220 --> 00:47:29.400 align:middle line:90%
Better yet, horse's milk.

00:47:29.400 --> 00:47:31.760 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: But you're talking
about raw goat's milk,

00:47:31.760 --> 00:47:33.460 align:middle line:10%
raw cow's milk, raw--

00:47:33.460 --> 00:47:34.270 align:middle line:10%
>>ROM: No, I'm not
even talking about raw.

00:47:34.270 --> 00:47:35.070 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Even pasteurized?

00:47:35.070 --> 00:47:36.340 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: Even pasteurized.

00:47:36.340 --> 00:47:43.910 align:middle line:84%
You got to know that raw food is
frowned upon by the government

00:47:43.910 --> 00:47:46.970 align:middle line:84%
because, truthfully,
raw food if it's

00:47:46.970 --> 00:47:49.810 align:middle line:84%
handled by the wrong
processors, could have E coli,

00:47:49.810 --> 00:47:52.090 align:middle line:90%
could have bad bacteria in it.

00:47:52.090 --> 00:47:54.030 align:middle line:90%
I'm a big believer in raw food.

00:47:54.030 --> 00:47:57.200 align:middle line:84%
But as a public servant,
I can't rightfully

00:47:57.200 --> 00:48:00.140 align:middle line:84%
say that all raw
food is good for you.

00:48:00.140 --> 00:48:02.580 align:middle line:90%
At certain times--

00:48:02.580 --> 00:48:03.705 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Know your source.

00:48:03.705 --> 00:48:04.360 align:middle line:90%
Use your discretion.

00:48:04.360 --> 00:48:05.401 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: -pasturized foods.

00:48:05.401 --> 00:48:06.330 align:middle line:90%
Use your discretion.

00:48:06.330 --> 00:48:08.470 align:middle line:84%
But when the bacteria
get onto the food,

00:48:08.470 --> 00:48:10.280 align:middle line:84%
they will actually
create this food

00:48:10.280 --> 00:48:13.150 align:middle line:84%
into a living raw food
again, because they're

00:48:13.150 --> 00:48:15.510 align:middle line:84%
breaking the food down
and they're excreting it,

00:48:15.510 --> 00:48:18.110 align:middle line:90%
and now it's raw again.

00:48:18.110 --> 00:48:20.670 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean, we are
only just a little way

00:48:20.670 --> 00:48:22.980 align:middle line:84%
through all the questions
I have to ask you.

00:48:22.980 --> 00:48:24.600 align:middle line:84%
That one is really
fascinating, so I

00:48:24.600 --> 00:48:26.340 align:middle line:84%
think people have
gotten enough on that.

00:48:26.340 --> 00:48:29.060 align:middle line:84%
They can go check out your site
and figure out what to do next.

00:48:29.060 --> 00:48:32.000 align:middle line:84%
But let's talk about what
happens in the mouth.

00:48:32.000 --> 00:48:36.260 align:middle line:84%
So many people have breakdowns
in the mouth and are-- I mean,

00:48:36.260 --> 00:48:37.870 align:middle line:84%
all the new technology
in dentistry

00:48:37.870 --> 00:48:39.889 align:middle line:84%
is coming along to
compensate for it.

00:48:39.889 --> 00:48:41.430 align:middle line:84%
Oh, if you lose your
teeth that's OK.

00:48:41.430 --> 00:48:43.000 align:middle line:84%
We'll just peg a
new one in there.

00:48:43.000 --> 00:48:46.780 align:middle line:84%
But what's happening on a
bacteria level in the mouth?

00:48:46.780 --> 00:48:49.560 align:middle line:10%
>>ROM: On a bacterial
levels so far identified

00:48:49.560 --> 00:48:52.970 align:middle line:10%
are about 800 different species
of microbes that naturally live

00:48:52.970 --> 00:48:56.700 align:middle line:10%
in the mouth, and they
naturally call the oral cavity

00:48:56.700 --> 00:48:57.560 align:middle line:10%
their home.

00:48:57.560 --> 00:48:59.470 align:middle line:10%
And believe it or
not, the microbes

00:48:59.470 --> 00:49:01.380 align:middle line:10%
that live inside the
mouth are completely

00:49:01.380 --> 00:49:03.930 align:middle line:10%
different from the microbes
that live on our skin, which

00:49:03.930 --> 00:49:06.550 align:middle line:10%
are completely different
from the microbes in our gut.

00:49:06.550 --> 00:49:08.790 align:middle line:10%
The microbes in our
gut is like the ocean.

00:49:08.790 --> 00:49:10.340 align:middle line:10%
The microbes in our
mouth is kind of

00:49:10.340 --> 00:49:14.189 align:middle line:10%
like the edge of the oceans,
kind of like the beach.

00:49:14.189 --> 00:49:15.730 align:middle line:10%
And again, there
are different plants

00:49:15.730 --> 00:49:19.700 align:middle line:10%
that grow on the edge of the
beach versus down in the ocean.

00:49:19.700 --> 00:49:21.550 align:middle line:10%
And the microbes
that are on our skin

00:49:21.550 --> 00:49:23.950 align:middle line:10%
is kind of like the desert.

00:49:23.950 --> 00:49:28.330 align:middle line:84%
The microbes in our armpits
is kind of like the jungle.

00:49:28.330 --> 00:49:30.810 align:middle line:90%
And they're different microbes.

00:49:30.810 --> 00:49:33.800 align:middle line:84%
You and I are more closely
related genetically

00:49:33.800 --> 00:49:38.190 align:middle line:84%
than the microbes on my skin are
to the microbes inside my nose

00:49:38.190 --> 00:49:40.270 align:middle line:84%
and the microbes
inside my mouth.

00:49:40.270 --> 00:49:42.230 align:middle line:84%
They are so different
genetically.

00:49:42.230 --> 00:49:46.990 align:middle line:84%
So you have to imagine that the
microbial species in the mouth

00:49:46.990 --> 00:49:48.480 align:middle line:90%
are there to protect the mouth.

00:49:48.480 --> 00:49:50.760 align:middle line:84%
They need that
mouth to be healthy.

00:49:50.760 --> 00:49:52.840 align:middle line:84%
And every time we
take in products

00:49:52.840 --> 00:49:56.109 align:middle line:84%
that kill all the microbes,
these antiseptic mouthwashes,

00:49:56.109 --> 00:49:57.900 align:middle line:84%
every time they take
them in, they actually

00:49:57.900 --> 00:49:59.330 align:middle line:90%
kill all the microbes.

00:49:59.330 --> 00:50:01.210 align:middle line:90%
It's really bad for you.

00:50:01.210 --> 00:50:02.990 align:middle line:84%
It kills all the
microbes in your mouth.

00:50:02.990 --> 00:50:04.860 align:middle line:84%
And what happens is
any time you take

00:50:04.860 --> 00:50:06.910 align:middle line:84%
in the next spoonful
of food that you're

00:50:06.910 --> 00:50:08.700 align:middle line:84%
taking in your
mouth, it's actually

00:50:08.700 --> 00:50:13.040 align:middle line:84%
filled with millions of microbes
that don't live in the mouth.

00:50:13.040 --> 00:50:16.430 align:middle line:84%
So when you clean your mouth
out and sterilize your mouth out

00:50:16.430 --> 00:50:20.850 align:middle line:84%
with these antiseptic
tooth washes, mouthwashes,

00:50:20.850 --> 00:50:27.340 align:middle line:84%
and these toothpastes that have
this antibiotic in it-- which

00:50:27.340 --> 00:50:29.070 align:middle line:84%
I'll go into that
in a little bit--

00:50:29.070 --> 00:50:30.529 align:middle line:84%
it kills out all
the good microbes.

00:50:30.529 --> 00:50:32.111 align:middle line:84%
And then when you
eat the bad microbes

00:50:32.111 --> 00:50:34.480 align:middle line:84%
through your next burger or
through your next milkshake,

00:50:34.480 --> 00:50:36.819 align:middle line:90%
they set up shop in your mouth.

00:50:36.819 --> 00:50:38.610 align:middle line:84%
And they don't have
anything that-- there's

00:50:38.610 --> 00:50:42.100 align:middle line:84%
no one there to
defend the territory.

00:50:42.100 --> 00:50:45.130 align:middle line:84%
And no wonder the pockets
inside your mouth gets

00:50:45.130 --> 00:50:47.110 align:middle line:84%
filled with these
anaerobic bacteria.

00:50:47.110 --> 00:50:50.290 align:middle line:84%
So what we found is by flooding
your mouth with the microbes

00:50:50.290 --> 00:50:53.200 align:middle line:84%
that naturally live in there
and gotten from the people that

00:50:53.200 --> 00:50:55.920 align:middle line:84%
have no tooth decay, those
are really strong microbes.

00:50:55.920 --> 00:50:58.080 align:middle line:84%
We have a product called
Oralive that actually

00:50:58.080 --> 00:51:00.370 align:middle line:84%
have these like
microbial products

00:51:00.370 --> 00:51:02.580 align:middle line:84%
in the mouth that
actually set up

00:51:02.580 --> 00:51:05.200 align:middle line:84%
shop for these microbes,
the natural microbes

00:51:05.200 --> 00:51:07.030 align:middle line:84%
to start rebuilding
themselves and set up

00:51:07.030 --> 00:51:07.740 align:middle line:90%
their defenses again.

00:51:07.740 --> 00:51:09.489 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And there's
another rub to that.

00:51:09.489 --> 00:51:11.750 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I've been using
that for about a year.

00:51:11.750 --> 00:51:16.330 align:middle line:84%
And initially, you look in
the jar, it looks like mud

00:51:16.330 --> 00:51:18.650 align:middle line:90%
and it's a little bit gritty.

00:51:18.650 --> 00:51:22.240 align:middle line:84%
And the thing is, you don't
just brush your teeth with it.

00:51:22.240 --> 00:51:23.990 align:middle line:84%
You actually swish it
around in your mouth

00:51:23.990 --> 00:51:26.156 align:middle line:84%
when you put the water in
where you'd normally rinse

00:51:26.156 --> 00:51:27.935 align:middle line:84%
and spit out, and
then you drink that.

00:51:27.935 --> 00:51:29.050 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: You swallow it.

00:51:29.050 --> 00:51:30.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, you swallow it.

00:51:30.890 --> 00:51:32.680 align:middle line:90%
Now I do that.

00:51:32.680 --> 00:51:34.700 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's not gross
or anything like that,

00:51:34.700 --> 00:51:37.700 align:middle line:84%
but that's starting to
repopulate down into the guts

00:51:37.700 --> 00:51:39.280 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:51:39.280 --> 00:51:42.400 align:middle line:84%
>>ROM: So when most people
think about spitting out

00:51:42.400 --> 00:51:45.630 align:middle line:84%
the toothpaste or doing this
practice called oil pulling,

00:51:45.630 --> 00:51:47.700 align:middle line:84%
where you spit out
this sesame oil,

00:51:47.700 --> 00:51:49.820 align:middle line:84%
you're spitting out
all the bad microbes.

00:51:49.820 --> 00:51:52.140 align:middle line:84%
But when you're eating an
apple-- think about it.

00:51:52.140 --> 00:51:53.598 align:middle line:84%
When you're eating
an apple, you're

00:51:53.598 --> 00:51:55.900 align:middle line:84%
literally brushing your
teeth because you're

00:51:55.900 --> 00:51:57.930 align:middle line:84%
scraping all the
bacteria off of your gums

00:51:57.930 --> 00:51:59.180 align:middle line:90%
and then you swallow it.

00:51:59.180 --> 00:52:01.940 align:middle line:84%
So it's basically like
swallowing toothpaste.

00:52:01.940 --> 00:52:06.085 align:middle line:84%
My grandfather imparted a note
of wisdom to me before he died.

00:52:06.085 --> 00:52:08.210 align:middle line:84%
He basically said, don't
put anything in your mouth

00:52:08.210 --> 00:52:10.300 align:middle line:90%
that you have to spit out.

00:52:10.300 --> 00:52:11.450 align:middle line:90%
He was a Jehovah's Witness.

00:52:11.450 --> 00:52:12.870 align:middle line:90%
He didn't like taking in drugs.

00:52:12.870 --> 00:52:14.549 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's good advice.

00:52:14.549 --> 00:52:16.340 align:middle line:84%
But then, you better
be diligent about what

00:52:16.340 --> 00:52:17.580 align:middle line:84%
you put in your
mouth to begin with.

00:52:17.580 --> 00:52:18.210 align:middle line:90%
>>ROM: That's right.

00:52:18.210 --> 00:52:18.751 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:52:18.751 --> 00:52:20.710 align:middle line:84%
And what the
toothpaste we have now,

00:52:20.710 --> 00:52:24.270 align:middle line:84%
the fluoride in your mouth,
that's not the only way to kill

00:52:24.270 --> 00:52:26.900 align:middle line:90%
cavities.

00:52:26.900 --> 00:52:29.930 align:middle line:84%
The American Dental
Association and the industry

00:52:29.930 --> 00:52:32.600 align:middle line:84%
would have us think that
fluoride is the only way

00:52:32.600 --> 00:52:34.940 align:middle line:84%
to kill cavities and to
keep your mouth fresh,

00:52:34.940 --> 00:52:37.680 align:middle line:84%
when it's actually
one of many ways.

00:52:37.680 --> 00:52:39.780 align:middle line:84%
And it's actually one
of the poorer ways

00:52:39.780 --> 00:52:41.640 align:middle line:84%
